name: Adam Cooper
tweet: Whatever side you are on, @LewisHamilton or @Max33Verstappen, there's a bigger picture. Sunday night should have been the greatest day ever for F1 in terms of global TV attention, attracting new fans, showing the world why we love it so much. And the sport blew it...

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: Toto Wolff on the restart: "It was a freestyle reading of the rules and it left Lewis like a sitting duck."

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: @xandermcbride The SC gave Max back the 11.9 second gap. Was that fair to Lewis? Was Max getting a free change fair? Max could have also changed again to have even fresher tyres for the restart. And I think Max would have taken starting P2, on the same tyres, right behind Lewis...

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: 2. Charlie Whiting did it at Monaco in 2011 when told it would take "20 minutes" to get Petrov out of his car, and Michael Masi did it in Baku this year, giving us that one lap race. The option is always there, but it won't hurt to see it properly written into the regs.

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: 1. The FIA investigation should also look specifying a procedure in the rules for red flagging the race in the closing laps to ensure that we get a standing restart and green flag finish, even if not required on safety grounds or due to track blockage etc.

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: I hope the investigation addresses radio intimidation of the race director by showboating team bosses - that has to stop. Traditionally there is one voice from pit wall to race control, the sporting director/team manager, and that should now be properly formalised in the rules.

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: As I said last night, a withdrawal of the appeal was the inevitable next step after @JeanTodt promised @MercedesAMGF1 an investigation. Let's hope it is a proper one and really digs into the timeline of what happened and how and why calls were made:  https://t.co/rDMQmHiTAh

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: '@MercedesAMGF1: "Lewis, you are the greatest racer in the history of F1 and you drove your heart out for every lap of this incredible season. You're a flawless sportsman on and off the track and you delivered a faultless performance."

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: '@MercedesAMGF1: "To Max Verstappen and RBR: we would like to express our sincere respect for your achievements this season. You made this F1 title fight truly epic. Max, we congratulate you & your entire team. We look forward to taking the fight to you on the track next season."

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: Merc: "We appealed in the interest of sporting fairness, and we have since been in a constructive dialogue with the FIA and Formula 1 to create clarity for the future, so that all competitors know the rules under which they are racing, and how they will be enforced."

name: Adam Cooper
tweet: '@MercedesAMGF1: "The Mercedes-AMG Petronas team will actively work with this commission to build a better Formula 1 - for every team and every fan who loves this sport as much as we do. We will hold the FIA accountable for this process and we hereby withdraw our appeal."
